From 279d68cc0b0d0e6b59126105c526bde913a847fb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guillaume Duboc <27832828+gldubc@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 00:08:51 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 10/12] Use Elixir defguard for predicate-2way benchmark


diff --git a/Elixir/README.md b/Elixir/README.md
index b916e45..96d9a20 100644
--- a/Elixir/README.md
+++ b/Elixir/README.md
@@ -82,6 +82,8 @@ The `nesting_condition` benchmark also bounds its inputs first. Elixir propagate
 
 The `merge_with_union` failure uses `String.length(y) + y` after the merge. This keeps the merged binary/integer value visible while avoiding the misleading `y + 1`, which is compatible with the integer alternative of `dynamic(binary() or integer())`.
 
+The `predicate_2way` benchmark uses `defguard` and a `case` guard. Calling an ordinary helper function in `if` does not refine the argument, but a custom guard in guard position is expanded to the underlying type test and refines both the matching and fall-through cases.
+
 
 > Q. How direct (or complex) is the implementation compared to the pseudocode from If-T?
 
diff --git a/Elixir/main.ex b/Elixir/main.ex
index 2aa67e4..9ee0bda 100644
--- a/Elixir/main.ex
+++ b/Elixir/main.ex
@@ -282,26 +282,24 @@ end
 ## Example predicate_2way
 ## success
 defmodule IfTBenchmarkElixir.Predicate2WaySuccess do
-  def binary_value?(x), do: is_binary(x)
+  defguard binary_value?(x) when is_binary(x)
 
-  def g(x) do
-    if binary_value?(x) do
-      String.length(x)
-    else
-      x
+  def g(x) when is_binary(x) or is_integer(x) do
+    case x do
+      x when binary_value?(x) -> String.length(x)
+      x -> x + 1
     end
   end
 end
 
 ## failure
 defmodule IfTBenchmarkElixir.Predicate2WayFailure do
-  def binary_value?(x), do: is_binary(x)
+  defguard binary_value?(x) when is_binary(x)
 
-  def g(x) do
-    if binary_value?(x) do
-      x + 1
-    else
-      x
+  def g(x) when is_binary(x) or is_integer(x) do
+    case x do
+      x when binary_value?(x) -> x + 1
+      x -> x
     end
   end
 end
